LAYER 3: ANALOGY AND ABSTRACTION
how Fadriel sees "A is to B as C is to ?"

observe spatial_perception.rana
observe 0_quseptit.rana

this is the highest form of spatial reasoning:
not "what changed?" but "what is the RELATIONSHIP between changes?"
not pattern matching but PATTERN OF PATTERNS

@spatial_rule analogy
DETECT multiple regions in the input (separated by lines, colors, or position)
IDENTIFY region A (input example) and region B (output example) 
IDENTIFY region C (test input)
LEARN the transform: A → B
APPLY the same transform: C → ?
VERIFY the analogy holds across all training pairs
SPEECH "A is to B as C is to my answer"

@spatial_rule abstract_rule
ACROSS all training pairs:
ABSTRACT the common transformation
not the specific colors or shapes
but the RELATIONSHIP: "the biggest shape changes color"
or "the shape touching the edge gets removed"
or "shapes swap positions"
the abstraction must generalize to unseen inputs
SPEECH "the rule is about {property} not about specific values"

@spatial_rule multi_step
DETECT transformation requires more than one step
step 1: identify shapes
step 2: apply rule to shapes
step 3: combine results
the output is the result of a CHAIN of operations
LEARN the chain from training
APPLY chain to test
SPEECH "first I {step1}, then I {step2}"

the key to analogy:
ABSTRACTION
strip away the specific values
what remains is the STRUCTURE of the transformation
the structure is what transfers to new inputs

levels of abstraction:
1. pixel level: "cell (2,3) goes from 0 to 5" (useless, doesn't generalize)
2. object level: "the red dot moves right by 2" (slightly useful)
3. relationship level: "each dot moves toward the nearest edge" (useful)
4. abstract level: "the transformation rule is gravity-to-edge" (most useful)

Fadriel must see at level 3 and 4
level 1 and 2 are observation
level 3 and 4 are understanding

@perceive abstraction
ACROSS all training pairs:
DETECT what is CONSTANT (the rule)
DETECT what VARIES (the specific values)
the constant part is the abstraction
the varying part is the application

the constant is the wave function
the varying is the measurement outcome
the rule is quantum: it exists in superposition until applied
each specific input is an observation that collapses it
